{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f7ea7e31-4f60-4be3-a779-47878f18dc16","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the default **test ID generation strategy**. Tests now get fully-qualified IDs, so ADO treats them as brand-new. To restore history, add to your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</MSTest>\n```\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level context** — it no longer carries test-specific properties. Accessing `TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException` because class init runs once for the class, not per-test.\n\nYour fix — remove or guard that access:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is not available here in v4\n    // Use context.FullyQualifiedTestClassName instead, or\n    // move test-name logic to [TestInitialize]\n}\n```\n\n## Other v4 things to watch out for\n\n| Change | Impact |\n|--------|--------|\n| `[DataRow]` display name format changed | Parameterized test names look different; may affect filters/ADO tracking |\n| `Assert.ThrowsException` generic constraint tightened | Some edge-case usages won't compile |\n| `DeploymentItem` behavior | No longer copies by default in some project layouts |\n| Default timeout is now `Timeout.Infinite` explicitly | Tests that relied on implicit framework timeout may hang |\n| `[ClassCleanup]` timing | Now defaults to `EndOfClass` (was `EndOfAssembly` in v3) — cleanup runs sooner |\n\nIf you just want to unblock quickly, the runsettings tweak + moving `TestName` access to `[TestInitialize]` will resolve your two immediate issues.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c23cb64-a195-4684-827e-8bd7cf77af66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I can provide a comprehensive answer about the known MSTest v4 breaking changes the user is experiencing. Let me address both issues and mention other things to watch out for.\n\n1. **Test history lost in Azure DevOps**: MSTest v4 changed the default test ID generation. Previously, test IDs were based on a legacy format; now they use fully qualified names. This means ADO sees them as entirely new tests. The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` to `Legacy` in the runsettings or project file.\n\n2. **TestContext.TestName in [ClassInitialize]**: In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a \"class-level\" context that doesn't have test-specific information (since it runs once for the class, not per-test). Accessing `TestName` will throw `InvalidOperationException`. \n\nThis is intentional — the context no longer exposes test-specific data when operating at the class level. I should walk through the fixes for both issues and help them understand what changed.","outputTokens":735,"requestId":"BC31:28FA24:20E37EA:24C6A41:69FAAAFE"},"id":"bbb2d649-d301-48a6-b5ba-3547d2b5a228","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:44:30.620Z","parentId":"a4e96a07-00c6-494b-af0c-efef4049dc3e"}
